transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you so much for calling Viagra at Score Blue. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I want to cancel my subscription.

Speaker 1: Yes, sir. I can help you with that. I need your full name and date of birth.

Speaker 2: James Hayes, March 10th, 1963.

Speaker 1: James, bear with me while I pull up your prescription.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Mr. Hayes, your prescription was initially written back in November for the 50 milligram Viagra, a GV.

Speaker 2: Did a quantity of 25 and he opted in for the larger order as well, correct?

Speaker 1: Yeah, it's not working for me, so I need to cancel.

Speaker 2: Sure, I understand. Frustrated, that can be for sure.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: And did you attempt to take two of the pills by chance, Mr. Hayes?

Speaker 1: That's yeah, by the doctor.

Speaker 2: Empty stomach, right? No alcohol, correct?

Speaker 1: And you're also still taking the testosterone, right?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I still am. I'm still doing TRT.

Speaker 1: Okay. So James, when you placed this order—

Speaker 2: Were you aware you were getting generic sildenafil, not the a GV?

Speaker 1: No, I was—I thought I was getting a GV. That's what I thought I ordered. That's why I went to your website.

Speaker 2: Uh-huh. No, so Score Blue sells—yeah, Alice, we sell generic Viagra.

Speaker 1: We sell a GV and we sell name-brand, the blue pill, right? Blue pills are $99 a pop.

Speaker 2: I'm looking at your profile because when you said it wasn't effective, I was supposed to—your health survey—

Speaker 1: You notice that, you know, it used to work ten years ago and he said these aren't working for you.

Speaker 2: So I did some research. So I think about what might have happened is you might have ordered this adenofil generic on accident.

Speaker 1: If that's the case, James, would you like me to send you an order of the a GV to try it?

Speaker 2: At least this would be for free.

Speaker 1: So then you have the opportunity to try the proper medication.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I thought that's what I was taking. I thought that's a pain—no, I think what you—I mean—

Speaker 1: You can tell me, but I mean, unless you received something else—

Speaker 2: I see here that prescription was written for generic sildenafil.

Speaker 1: And—

Speaker 2: That was what I liked on the system online. Do you have the pills in front of you?

Speaker 1: No, they're there—

Speaker 2: I'm in the middle of a work trip, so—

Speaker 1: Okay. Okay. I guess that it would be—there'd be no skin off your back.

Speaker 2: Really, I would send you 25 of the a GV.

Speaker 1: Which would be, like I said, a stronger medication than what you currently received.

Speaker 2: I think, and if that's what you meant to order, you know, we just put your—

Speaker 1: No, I thought—I thought I was getting a TV. That was the whole reason I—you know, I contacted you guys.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: So I'll send you replacements. I'm going to get you 25 of the a GV.

Speaker 2: Okay, I can also, if you're comfortable with it, I can jump that up to a hundred milligrams.

Speaker 1: So then you can take one pill and see how that works for you, so you don't have to be stacking them.

Speaker 2: It is completely safe to take one if you're—I can do 50 milligrams for you, 25, 50—

Speaker 1: But I can also do the same, you know, honor it at a hundred milligrams.

Speaker 2: Okay, just do the hundred. We'll see if that works. Yeah, I want to—I want to get something working for you.

Speaker 1: That's my biggest concern here. Okay, so I'm going to get you those replacements.

Speaker 2: I'm gonna put your account on a pause.

Speaker 1: Okay, so it's gonna be paused until August.

Speaker 2: I want to try the a GV, get back to me and let me know how it works for you.

Speaker 1: Okay. Thanks.

Speaker 2: Okay, anything else I can do for you today?

Speaker 1: No, that'll do it.

Speaker 2: All right. Thanks, James. Appreciate you. Have a good rest of your day.

Speaker 1: All right, you too.
